  "text": "with an Aviv 202SF CD spectrophotometer. Isothermal Titration Calorimetry (ITC) Measurement. A Nano ITC (TA Instruments) system was used to investigate the interactions between ISCU(M108I) and (NIA) [CITATION_1] . Both (NIA) [CITATION_2] and ISCU(M108I) were dialyzed extensively against HNT buffer. The sample cell (169 μL) contained 0.1 mM ISCU(M108I), and the syringe (50 μL) contained 1.1 mM (NIA) 2 . Twenty aliquots of 2.5 μL of (NIA) [CITATION_3] were injected into the sample cell, and the heat generated after each injection was measured. NanoAnalyse software was used in processing and fitting the ITC data.",
